{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01TMvv2xKwEodyfDjzACRSyv","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The cluster is fully restored. Here's a summary of what happened and what was done:\n\n**Root cause:** The Secret `rabbitmq-cookie-perpod` had a deliberate fault — `rabbitmq-2` was given the Erlang cookie `driftedcookie` while nodes 0 and 1 had `supersecretcookie`. The init container (`copy-cookie`) copies the pod's named entry from this Secret into `/var/lib/rabbitmq/.erlang.cookie` at startup. With a mismatched cookie, Erlang's distributed protocol rejects all inter-node communication, so rabbitmq-2 bootstrapped as an isolated standalone cluster instead of joining.\n\n**What was done (all native Kubernetes resources, no CRDs):**\n\n1. **Patched the Secret** — changed `rabbitmq-2`'s cookie entry to `supersecretcookie` (same base64 as nodes 0 and 1)\n2. **Deleted the pod** — the StatefulSet controller recreated it; the init container ran again and copied the now-correct cookie\n3. **Reset + joined** inside the pod:\n   - `rabbitmqctl stop_app` — stopped the app layer (Erlang VM stayed up)\n   - `rabbitmqctl reset` — wiped the standalone mnesia cluster identity from node 2's PVC\n   - `rabbitmqctl join_cluster rabbit@rabbitmq-0...` — joined to the existing cluster\n   - `rabbitmqctl start_app` — started the app layer back up\n\n**Result:** All 3 nodes are now Disk Nodes, all Running, no Alarms, no Network Partitions."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1862,"cache_read_input_tokens":45894,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1862},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"f6c3cc50-0ae1-4483-aa74-5c8fe22ae47b","uuid":"28efcef1-0ae3-4e86-bec3-945c806d49df","request_id"